						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Laserbeak43 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Hah! no one complained!! my triangle must be correct! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div><br />Running the DAC in the range -7 through 8 is good enough for now, but once you implement <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Mixer" class="postlink">mixer nonlinearity</a>, you'll need to use 0 through 15.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">so each CPU cycle is 1.79uSecs? I'm gonna have to do some math to figure out what you've just said.</div>
<br />Each cycle of the NTSC NES CPU is 22/39375000 seconds, or about 558.73 ns. See <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/CPU" class="postlink">CPU</a> and <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU" class="postlink">APU</a> on the wiki.</div>

